[3] Brazil (Espirito Santo), horses
Date: Fri 24 Apr 2015
Source: G1 [in Portuguese, excerpts trans. Mod.JW, edited]
http://g1.globo.com/espirito-santo/noticia/2015/04/cavalos-da-pm-infectados-com-mormo-vao-ser-sacrificados-no-es.html


Military Police horses infected with glanders will be sacrificed in Espirito Santo
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11 Military Police horses will be euthanized after being infected with glanders. All police horses are in quarantine since 31 Mar [2015]. The disease is caused by bacteria that infect horses, donkeys and mules and can be transmitted to humans.

The Agricultural Protection Institute (IDAF) awaits the outcome of examination of the 65 horses of the Sierra Breeding Center. According to the head of the Animal Health Protection and Inspection Department (IDAF), Fabiano Fiuza, the institute has 2 main suspects for how the disease infected the police horses. In 2014, 2 horses spent 6 months training with the army in Rio de Janeiro. In addition, in 2013, an outbreak of glanders in the police Cavalry of Espirito Santo contaminated 25 horses.

The past 2 years, 51 horses infected by glanders were sacrificed in the state; 25 were military police horses. The Police said mounted police will be replaced by motorcycle or car police where there were horseback patrols.

